The Cybersecurity Bootcamp at 4Geeks Academy is designed to help individuals become cybersecurity specialists, even without prior knowledge in the field. The program provides a solid foundation in Windows, Linux, network, and server administration, as well as practical skills for securing these environments.

Participants will learn about cloud security, penetration testing (both offensive and defensive), and cyber threat intelligence analysis. The program also covers data loss prevention (DLP) strategies and compliance with international standards such as ISO 27001 and NIST.

The bootcamp lasts for 16 weeks and includes three live online classes per week. Class sizes are kept small with a maximum of 16 people to ensure personalized attention. Upon completion, participants receive an official 4Geeks Completion Certificate, recognized by multiple institutions.

No previous experience is required to enroll in the program. The median annual salary for cybersecurity professionals in the United States is $103,560, making it a promising field to pursue.

